Author: skelekey
Text: A diagnosis is just a label (unless you’re seeking treatment). Don’t let diagnostic requirements invalidate your feelings and struggles. Who gives a fuck if someone “doesn’t meet the weight criteria for anorexia” or something like that. Doesn’t mean you aren’t suffering, so don’t doubt your feelings.  It’s like saying, “i think I’m sick, I have a cough. But I’m not coughing up blood yet so it probably doesn’t matter.”

Author: notracisthasblackcat
Text: Yeah I'm not disordered enough to get diagnosed to be honest but if I told a therapist I don't think anyone would say my behaviors around food and weight are normal
